name: PerformanceTiming.unloadEventStart
description: The legacy PerformanceTiming.unloadEventStart read-only property returns an unsigned long long representing the moment, in miliseconds since the UNIX epoch, the unload event has been thrown. If there is no previous document, or if the previous document, or one of the needed redirects, is not of the same origin, the value returned is 0.
